-- HK store operator Lifestyle Intl shares fall 5.8 pct after Qatar buys stake 
-- 
-- Sun Oct 19, 2014 09:58PM EDT
-- None



SHANGHAI, Oct 20 (Reuters) - Shares in Hong Kong department store operator Lifestyle International Holdings <1212.HK> fell 5.8 percent in early trading after sovereign wealth fund Qatar Holding LLC said it would buy a HK$4.78 billion ($616.19 million) stake in the firm.

